Notebook[{

Cell[CellGroupData[{
Cell[TextData[StyleBox["Training a classifier for source attribution of \
campylobacteriosis", "Title"]], "Chapter",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.779632285014203*^9, 3.779632301509828*^9}, {
  3.7796345709478197`*^9, 
  3.7796345727073174`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"3caf72a6-7030-4f45-80fd-\
a3c87b157ff8"],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["Campylobacter",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " is a foodborne pathogen that is the largest  cause  of bacterial \
gastroenteritis in the developed world.\n\n",
 StyleBox["Campylobacter",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " is a zoonotic pathogen hosted by several animals including cattle, \
chicken, sheep, pig or wild birds. Food products from these animals represent \
a risk of infection to humans which can develop campylobacteriosis. If \
someone is infected, it is important to determine the origin of infection, \
i.e. which type of food is responsible for the transmission to the infected \
patient. If the source is identified, the authorities may decide to call back \
certain foods from the market to prevent further infections.\n\nThe aim of \
this practical is to use genomic data for ",
 StyleBox["Campylobacter",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " samples from five animal reservoirs (see Figure) to train a classifier so \
that infections in humans can be attributed to one of the five reservoirs. \
The ultimate goal is to use the classifier to determine the origin of ",
 StyleBox["Campylobacter",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " samples isolated from infected humans. In the dataset to be used, each \
sample is characterised by seven housekeeping genes for ",
 StyleBox["Campylobacter",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 ". Each gene is coded by a set of numbers (alleles). In practice, each \
sample is characterised by a feature vector consisting of 7 integer numbers. \
\n\nThe dataset contains Campylobacter samples isolated from humans and from \
animal reservoirs (cattle, chicken, sheep, pig and wild bird).  You will \
first deal with samples from animal reservoirs to train a classifier and test \
its performance. After that, you will be ready to attribute human isolates to \
food sources. \n\n",
 StyleBox["Practical suggestions:",
  FontWeight->"Bold"]
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.779633282603866*^9, 3.779633425013172*^9}, {
   3.7796336737201967`*^9, 3.77963385038927*^9}, {3.7796339036880817`*^9, 
   3.779633999126336*^9}, {3.779634453894651*^9, 3.779634564213438*^9}, {
   3.779634604935977*^9, 3.779634695334482*^9}, {3.779634743269003*^9, 
   3.7796347811754913`*^9}, {3.7798000681743746`*^9, 
   3.7798001742296867`*^9}, {3.779800206176262*^9, 3.779800437279134*^9}, 
   3.7798005100820103`*^9, {3.779800580840459*^9, 3.779800717406831*^9}, {
   3.779800829117405*^9, 3.7798009560995283`*^9}, {3.7798010311478977`*^9, 
   3.7798012036494403`*^9}, {3.7798012763676195`*^9, 3.779801411801775*^9}, {
   3.7799442638720684`*^9, 3.779944318098196*^9}, {3.7799447292941856`*^9, 
   3.779944772766225*^9}, {3.7799449251162777`*^9, 3.7799449273856306`*^9}, 
   3.8147692931636333`*^9},ExpressionUUID->"715d09a7-5d64-4abe-9d50-\
5d9c9cd6b672"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[TextData[{
 "Make sure that you understand the analysis of the ",
 StyleBox["Iris flowers",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 " done in lectures ",
 StyleBox["before attempting this practical",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 "!"
}], "Item",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.7799447752901025`*^9, 
  3.779944776748046*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"1e938794-c500-467a-87af-\
c0072b01afb6"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Names for ",
 StyleBox["new variables",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 " are normally ",
 StyleBox["suggested",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 " throughout the practical. This is done to be able to refer to such \
variables in forthcoming tasks of the practical. You are free to use other \
names but this might be confusing. In addition, the solutions to the \
practical provided later will use the suggested names and you might find \
useful to use the same names to compare."
}], "Item",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.7799447752901025`*^9, 
  3.7799449106151133`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"53d3fb3f-3b20-411e-9b88-\
5a97a5b4ccb9"]
}, Closed]],

