Cell[TextData[{
 "Here, ",
 StyleBox["f1", "CodeText"],
 " and ",
 StyleBox["f2", "CodeText"],
 " correspond to features (genes). ",
 StyleBox["source1", "CodeText"],
 " and ",
 StyleBox["source2", "CodeText"],
 " correspond to two reservoirs. "
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.779945807610292*^9, 3.779945808466236*^9}, {
  3.779945873469968*^9, 3.779945947023708*^9}, {3.779946747956052*^9, 
  3.7799467487770767`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"6b8f53f7-5fc2-4263-907d-\
4e2413452aec"],

Cell["\<\
In order to compare pairs of reservoirs, I suggest you proceed as follows:\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.779945957890603*^9, 
  3.779945999755192*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"7165dbb7-bcd8-4e77-b906-\
02553c10b9ea"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Make sure you understand how the plot is made.", "Item",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.779946007111696*^9, 
  3.7799460204147587`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"cc4e8685-3b3c-4cdb-97da-\
a87982e837c7"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Systematically compare the scatterplot for pairs of sources and pairs of \
genes. The comparison between sources in this case is not as clear as the \
comparison between species in the Iris flowers problem. However, we can \
extract some preliminary conclusions. ",
 StyleBox["Which sources do you think are more different from each other?",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 " These are the ones that the classifier you will train later should \
identify more accurately."
}], "Item",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.779946007111696*^9, 3.77994603175696*^9}, {
  3.7799460625194716`*^9, 3.7799460707511406`*^9}, {3.7799461589598846`*^9, 
  3.7799461628298306`*^9}, {3.7799464338644753`*^9, 
  3.7799465796698017`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"49035884-fb33-4dce-bac4-\
bdf09187fca7"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Answer", "Subsection",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.7799458310764866`*^9, 
  3.77994583226391*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"96e23caf-9c74-4429-b517-\
879e50ee0b29"],

Cell["\<\
Although it is not easy to identify clear trends in the data, one can observe \
the following:\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.779946698289183*^9, 3.779946742609132*^9}, {
  3.779946848139226*^9, 3.779946849281082*^9}, {3.779946934777026*^9, 
  3.7799469419723616`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"ee81d970-7240-42ba-b44f-\
57fc07c2bc7d"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["\<\
WB isolates are the ones that cover a larger part of the feature space. They \
seem to be quite different to other isolates. \
\>", "Item",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.779946963480762*^9, 3.779946976428569*^9}, {
  3.779947026702908*^9, 
  3.7799470694525366`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"1295da42-89b6-40e3-98e0-\
6fd5cd3d66ce"],

Cell["\<\
Pig isolates also cover a large region in the feature space and do not \
overlap much with other sources.\
\>", "Item",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.779946963480762*^9, 3.779946965674972*^9}, {
  3.7799470730874662`*^9, 
  3.779947140554644*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"8346e7d3-dc11-4cf4-bb34-\
28d780af213e"],

Cell["\<\
The point clouds for cattle and sheep seem to overlap more than those for any \
other sources. \
\>", "Item",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.779946963480762*^9, 3.779946965674972*^9}, {
  3.7799470730874662`*^9, 3.7799471847863364`*^9}, {3.779947275492161*^9, 
  3.779947275492161*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"99153837-abf1-49f0-8bdc-\
8e4fcaac590b"],

Cell["\<\
The point clouds for chicken does not spread over a region as wide as pig and \
WB but they seem to be reasonably separated from the clouds of other sources.\
\
\>", "Item",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.779946963480762*^9, 3.779946965674972*^9}, {
  3.7799470730874662`*^9, 3.7799471847863364`*^9}, {3.7799472762803173`*^9, 
  3.779947336633649*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"29a5ab23-b8c5-4a29-b102-\
9f1b451be277"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell["\<\
You may find useful to use a scatterplot with dynamical ranges as follows \
(make sure you understand how this is built):\
\>", "Text",
