Cell["\<\
Using the ClassifierMeasurements object obtained in the previous task, look \
at the following:\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.779972055971203*^9, 3.779972060838868*^9}, {
  3.7799721121458006`*^9, 
  3.7799722120743504`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"2e03ae83-a69f-4ee2-8b71-\
494c7a73f994"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Accuracy of the classifier", "Item",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.7799722249161997`*^9, 
  3.7799722306991825`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"d027bef2-9324-4167-9f9a-\
dee67e09309c"],

Cell["\<\
Confusion matrix. Comment on the results (e.g. which are the less confused \
classes? which are the most confused classes? Is confusion symmetric among \
classes? Can confusion be understood in terms of your exploration of the data \
in previous tasks in terms of scatter plots?). \
\>", "Item",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.7799722249161997`*^9, 3.779972271858409*^9}, {
  3.779972400306247*^9, 
  3.779972546713781*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"1c57a05a-d3f6-44f9-a4c6-\
ef9ddff58803"],

Cell["\<\
Calculate the true positive rate (TPR) for all the classes and plot the \
results in a bar chart with a bar for the TPR for each class (food \
reservoir). Comment on the meaning of TPR in this problem and discuss the \
results. \
\>", "Item",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.7799722249161997`*^9, 3.7799723913919525`*^9}, {
   3.779972588114125*^9, 3.779972719307424*^9}, {3.7799732752719607`*^9, 
   3.7799732752719607`*^9}, 
   3.814186614119954*^9},ExpressionUUID->"1e2b71a6-1c96-4c20-9b97-\
a59175110af3"]
}, Open  ]],

